**PocketType Build Guide\!**![][image1]

Step 1: Flash your controller- make a firmware file here by clicking the “compile” button: [https://config.qmk.fm/\#/evyd13/pockettype/LAYOUT\_ortho\_4x12](https://config.qmk.fm/#/evyd13/pockettype/LAYOUT_ortho_4x12)   
Brief flashing guide: download QMK toolbox, load above file, plug in controller, put board into bootloader (use tweezers to touch ground and reset together), click flash.

Step 2: Bend, fit and solder all the diodes- stripe should be towards the square pad

Step 3: Bend, fit and solder the two resistors. Orientation doesn’t matter.

Step 3: Fit all 48 switches. They’ll only go in one way. Solder them\! 

Step 4: Fit the two LEDs. The long leg is the positive and goes into the round hole.

Step 5: Fit and solder the header strips for the controller. Put the short side through the Pockettype PCB, leaving the long side pointing up. Solder just one pin until you are sure they are nice and straight and parallel to each other.

Step 6: Fit the controller onto the header strips. See above picture for correct orientation. Solder.

Step 7: Plug in and test. Fit key caps.

Step 8: Case assembly- see graphic below

Problems? Come and chat on our discord: [https://discord.gg/4F5UzK9hsJ](https://discord.gg/4F5UzK9hsJ)
